records.addlTxt:
2:41 PM; Case called for Hearing. Attorney Abbey Nickolie in court for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Danny Romero in court, in custody.  Attorney Nicholas M Weege in court for Danny Romero.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and confirms with counsel they are prepared to proceed to plea and sentencing today.  State recites the offer.  Atty. Weege confirms the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty. Court also orders cases 20CM1016 & 20CM1017 dismissed and read into this case.  Defendant may be returned to MSDF.  Any other future court dates will be removed from the calendar.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Weege.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
4 Months Jail (IF imposed consecutive to any other current sentence).

Term of Probation: 1 Year

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any assessments, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	No contact with CVS Store listed in the Criminal Complaint.
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription
-	Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they were prescribed;
-	Inform the Agent of all prescriptions;
-	No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact with any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed;
-	Obtain GED.  

COSTS:  $243.00;

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.
